Sarynth 22-Oct-18 07:08 AM
Two reasons for leaving, unity3d gave absolute control over developing a game, and valve editor tools crashed multiple times per day and made it (nearly) impossible to add something simple like emission to a baked model.
Made a lot of progress on various aspects of building an rpg game. Some good multiplayer networking stuff, but that was foiled by frustration with responsiveness and jerky motion that I made several attempts to solve but never really liked the solutions. Then I've created a nice UI, but probably taking a cumbersome path with how I'm building it. And, of course, when you control everything, you have to DO everything. I made some cool particles (I really like their particle editor, very similar to valve's but just more intuitive). And, made some really cool realistic nature environments. But, tying everything together was just going so slow. I wanted to work on gameplay. And, of course, realized I had gameplay here. I felt bad for folks that still to this day play it and ask for multiplayer to be fixed, so here I am.
Going to fix a few things, maybe release the last area. Add some stuff, and see how it goes. If I get the full map released, and add a couple cool features, maybe I'll try setting up a patreon to earn a little revenue. ( @Toyoka )
